JO  - Management Science
SP  - 978
EP  - 985
VL  - 23
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The problem of optimal planning of an electric power system is formulated as a cost minimizing mixed-integer mathematical program. The model emphasizes system reliability, requiring reserve generating capacity such that a Loss of Load Probability criterion of one day in ten years is met. Integer variables are used in the model to express system reliability explicitly as a constraint on the system model. Results are given for several plant outage rates and demand levels. The results show that the reliability and ?rule-of-thumb? approaches to system reserve planning can yield substantially different optimal system costs and configurations.
AB  - The problem of optimal planning of an electric power system is formulated as a cost minimizing mixed-integer mathematical program. The model emphasizes system reliability, requiring reserve generating capacity such that a Loss of Load Probability criterion of one day in ten years is met. Integer variables are used in the model to express system reliability explicitly as a constraint on the system model. Results are given for several plant outage rates and demand levels. The results show that the reliability and ?rule-of-thumb? approaches to system reserve planning can yield substantially different optimal system costs and configurations.
